### MED-03

**Severity:** 🟡 MEDIUM
**Title:** Crontab contains duplicated and conflicting entries

**Description:**
The root crontab (`sudo crontab -l`) contains two sets of entries for the same scripts, with different schedules. This appears to be the result of a previous configuration not being cleaned up after modification. Additionally, the user crontab contains two separate `@reboot` entries for `terminal64.exe` — one launching without a display variable and one with `DISPLAY=:20` — which will cause two MT5 instances to attempt to start on reboot.

**Evidence:**
```cron
# ROOT CRONTAB — duplicated entries (examples):
0 2 * * *   /usr/local/bin/system-maintenance.sh   # original: daily
0 2 * * 6   /usr/local/bin/system-maintenance.sh   # modified: Saturdays only
# Both are present — the daily one was never removed

0 1 * * 1   /usr/local/bin/safe-update.sh          # original: Mondays
0 4 * * 6   /usr/local/bin/safe-update.sh          # modified: Saturdays

# USER CRONTAB — duplicate MT5 launch:
@reboot sleep 15 && WINEPREFIX=... wine ".../terminal64.exe" > /dev/null 2>&1 &
@reboot sleep 30 && DISPLAY=:20 WINEPREFIX=... wine ".../terminal64.exe" >> /var/log/mt5_reboot.log 2>&1 &
```

**Impact:**
Duplicate cron entries cause scripts to run twice at different times, potentially causing conflicts in system maintenance operations. The double MT5 `@reboot` entry will launch two Wine/MT5 instances — the first without a valid `DISPLAY` variable will likely fail silently (output goes to `/dev/null`), but the process will consume resources and may interfere with the correct instance.

**Remediation:**
```bash
# Edit root crontab — keep only the Saturday-modified versions:
sudo crontab -e
# Remove:
# 0 2 * * *  /usr/local/bin/system-maintenance.sh  (keep the Saturday version)
# 0 3 * * 0  /usr/local/bin/nextcloud-backup.sh    (keep only one)
# 0 * * * *  /usr/local/bin/system-monitor.sh      (keep only one)
# 0 4 * * *  /usr/local/bin/security-check.sh      (keep only one)
# 0 1 * * 1  /usr/local/bin/safe-update.sh         (keep the Saturday version)

# Edit user crontab — keep only the correct MT5 entry:
crontab -e
# Remove the first @reboot entry (no DISPLAY, output to /dev/null)
# Keep: @reboot sleep 30 && DISPLAY=:20 WINEPREFIX=... >> /var/log/mt5_reboot.log 2>&1 &
```

